[normal]Annex A[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Public Health England Knowledge and Intelligence Service: Key products [bold]&#xa0;[bold]This annex sets out some of our key data and analysis tools.  All are available through the 
[normal]PHE [bold]d[bold]ata [bold]a[bold]nd knowledge gateway[bold]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Our tools and resources cover a broad range of public health areas, including:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We have a range of products that allow users to understand the health of their local populations and how health varies across the country. 
[normal] 
[normal]These include:
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Our stakeholders are asking for products tha
[normal]t can help them make the business case for investing in prevention and public health interventions, and can help them demonstrate effectiveness and cost effectiveness of the work that they are undertaking or proposing. 
[normal] 
[normal]Examples include: 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Health intelligence networks [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The heath in
[normal]telligence networks will provide wide-ranging, authoritative data, evidence and practice.  They will underpin improvement programmes for care quality and outcomes in line with national objectives.  There are five networks in development - 
[normal]can[bold]c[bold]e[bold]r[bold], cardiovascular disease, mental health, [bold]child and [bold]m[bold]at[bold]e[bold]rnal health[bold], [bold]and
[normal] [bold]end of lif[bold]e[bold] [bold]care[bold]. 
[normal] 
[normal]Health intelligence 
[normal]networks bring together many expert stakeholders and partners, including patient representatives and members of the public, to drive improvements in health and care in specific health areas.
